               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I know no more of it than the child unborn. I believe somebody might have put them in my pocket. I was not sober. I am a <rs id="t17710703-19-deflabel111" type="occupation">saddler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17710703-19-defend255 t17710703-19-deflabel111"></join> by business, I reside at Deal. I came up from Deal to get work at Putney.</p>
               <p>For the Prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17710703-19-person260">
                  Francis
                   Goodwin
               <interp inst="t17710703-19-person260" type="surname" value="Goodwin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710703-19-person260" type="given" value="Francis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710703-19-person260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a brewer in New-street, Shoe-lane; I have known him a twelve month: I have seen him about at houses I frequent in the brewing way; he was a serjeant in Elliot's light horse: he was a remarkable brave soldier, he has had a cut in his head; and when in liquor he is almost out of his senses.</p>
               <p>
            
